      <span class="faq-q-text">What is the difference between hreflang and the HTML lang attribute?</span>
      <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-a" id="what-is-the-difference-between-hreflang-and-the-ht"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>The HTML <code>lang</code> attribute (<code>&lt;html lang="en"&gt;</code>) tells browsers the page language for accessibility and text rendering. Hreflang tells search engines which alternate versions exist and which audience each version targets. Both serve different purposes. Use both on every page.</p></div></div>
  </div>
  <div class="faq-item">
    <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="does-hreflang-affect-google-rankings">
